{
  "name": "VoucherVault - Rail eTicket Auto-Import",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "sticky-1",
      "name": "Setup notes",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-120, 0],
      "parameters": {
        "width": 380,
        "height": 480,
        "content": "## Before you activate this\n\n1. **Gmail credential** — the 'Watch for Ticket Emails' node needs a Gmail OAuth2 credential. Add one under Credentials → New → Gmail OAuth2 API, then select it on that node.\n\n2. **VoucherVault API token** — on your VoucherVault server:\n   `docker compose exec app python manage.py drf_create_token <your-username>`\n   Then in n8n: Credentials → New → Header Auth, Name=`Authorization`, Value=`Token <the-token>`. Select it on the 'Create VoucherVault Item' node.\n\n3. **Gmail labels** — create two labels in Gmail first: `VoucherVault-Processed` and `VoucherVault-Failed`. The workflow applies these after each attempt so it never reprocesses an email (the trigger's search query already excludes anything labeled Processed).\n\n4. **Adjust the sender filter** on the trigger node to match who your tickets actually come from — the default targets Uber/Omio/Greater Anglia confirmation emails, edit the `q` field for other operators.\n\n5. **Test with 'Fetch Test Event' first** (right-click the trigger node) against a real ticket email before turning Active on, so you can see the HTTP Request node's actual response before it's creating items unattended.\n\nSee docs/RAIL_TICKET_IMPORT_SETUP.md in the VoucherVault repo for the full walkthrough."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "gmail-trigger-1",
      "name": "Watch for Ticket Emails",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.gmailTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1.2,
      "position": [280, 100],
      "parameters": {
        "pollTimes": {
          "item": [
            {
              "mode": "everyX",
              "value": 15,
              "unit": "minutes"
            }
          ]
        },
        "simple": false,
        "filters": {
          "q": "from:(uber.com OR omio.com OR greateranglia.co.uk OR trainline.com) has:attachment filename:pdf -label:VoucherVault-Processed -label:VoucherVault-Failed"
        },
        "downloadAttachments": true
      },
      "credentials": {
        "gmailOAuth2": {
          "id": "REPLACE_ME",
          "name": "Gmail account"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "code-1",
      "name": "Find PDF Attachment",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [520, 100],
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// Gmail Trigger names downloaded attachments after their own\n// attachment id, not a fixed key - find whichever binary property is\n// actually a PDF and re-key it to `file` so the HTTP Request node\n// downstream has one predictable field name to send, regardless of\n// how many attachments this specific email had or what they're named.\nfor (const item of $input.all()) {\n  const binary = item.binary || {};\n  const pdfKey = Object.keys(binary).find((key) => {\n    const b = binary[key];\n    return (b.mimeType || '').toLowerCase().includes('pdf')\n      || (b.fileName || '').toLowerCase().endsWith('.pdf');\n  });\n  if (pdfKey && pdfKey !== 'file') {\n    item.binary.file = item.binary[pdfKey];\n  }\n}\nreturn $input.all();"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "if-1",
      "name": "Has PDF?",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 2.2,
      "position": [760, 100],
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": {
            "caseSensitive": true,
            "leftValue": "",
            "typeValidation": "loose"
          },
          "conditions": [
            {
              "id": "cond-1",
              "leftValue": "={{ $binary.file !== undefined }}",
              "rightValue": "true",
              "operator": {
                "type": "boolean",
                "operation": "true",
                "singleValue": true
              }
            }
          ],
          "combinator": "and"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "http-1",
      "name": "Create VoucherVault Item",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.2,
      "position": [1000, 40],
      "onError": "continueErrorOutput",
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "https://voucher.nasmatrix.app/api/v1/imports/rail-ticket/",
        "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
        "genericAuthType": "httpHeaderAuth",
        "sendBody": true,
        "contentType": "multipart-form-data",
        "bodyParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            {
              "parameterType": "formBinaryData",
              "name": "file",
              "inputDataFieldName": "file"
            },
            {
              "name": "create",
              "value": "true"
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {
          "timeout": 30000
        }
      },
      "credentials": {
        "httpHeaderAuth": {
          "id": "REPLACE_ME",
          "name": "VoucherVault API Token"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "gmail-label-ok",
      "name": "Label: Processed",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.gmail",
      "typeVersion": 2.1,
      "position": [1260, -60],
      "parameters": {
        "resource": "message",
        "operation": "addLabels",
        "messageId": "={{ $('Watch for Ticket Emails').item.json.id }}",
        "labelIds": [],
        "labelNames": ["VoucherVault-Processed"]
      },
      "credentials": {
        "gmailOAuth2": {
          "id": "REPLACE_ME",
          "name": "Gmail account"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "gmail-label-fail",
      "name": "Label: Failed",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.gmail",
      "typeVersion": 2.1,
      "position": [1260, 160],
      "parameters": {
        "resource": "message",
        "operation": "addLabels",
        "messageId": "={{ $('Watch for Ticket Emails').item.json.id }}",
        "labelIds": [],
        "labelNames": ["VoucherVault-Failed"]
      },
      "credentials": {
        "gmailOAuth2": {
          "id": "REPLACE_ME",
          "name": "Gmail account"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "noop-not-pdf",
      "name": "No PDF - skip",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.noOp",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [1000, 260],
      "parameters": {}
    }
  ],
  "connections": {
    "Watch for Ticket Emails": {
      "main": [
        [
          {
            "node": "Find PDF Attachment",
            "type": "main",
            "index": 0
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    "Find PDF Attachment": {
      "main": [
        [
          {
            "node": "Has PDF?",
            "type": "main",
            "index": 0
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    "Has PDF?": {
      "main": [
        [
          {
            "node": "Create VoucherVault Item",
            "type": "main",
            "index": 0
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "node": "No PDF - skip",
            "type": "main",
            "index": 0
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    "Create VoucherVault Item": {
      "main": [
        [
          {
            "node": "Label: Processed",
            "type": "main",
            "index": 0
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "node": "Label: Failed",
            "type": "main",
            "index": 0
          }
        ]
      ]
    }
  },
  "active": false,
  "settings": {
    "executionOrder": "v1"
  },
  "pinData": {}
}
